exclamation marks are for one of the most beautiful combinations in chess
history, which was started with this move. But objectively the search for
beauty created unnecessary complications.} (17. Ng3 {
}
17... Qh6 18. Bc1 Qe6 19. Bc4 Nd5 (19... Qg6 20. Nh4 Qg4 21. Bxf7+) 20. Ng5 Qg4
21. Re4 {would finish the game without any troubles, but then chess would have
lost one of the jewels from it's crown!}) 17... gxf6 18. exf6 Rg8 $1 {At first sight an open g-file
